        "content": [
          "   Phrasal verbs are the part of English",
          "   that never stopped growing. Every",
          "   year, new ones appear. Nobody sits",
          "   down and invents 'commence' anymore.",
          "   But 'chill out', 'ghost someone',",
          "   'level up' — these were all born in",
          "   living memory.",
          "",
          "   They work by taking a plain Germanic",
          "   verb and adding a direction. Give +",
          "   up. Find + out. Put + off. Small",
          "   parts, endless combinations.",
          "",
          "   They're also what Latin can't do.",
          "   'Surrender' is a noun pretending to",
          "   be a verb. 'Give up' is the thing",
          "   itself — the hand opening, the",
          "   letting go, happening in real time."
        ],
